<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>She pulls aside each plaque, revealing a couple sheets of paper taped to the back, which she turns towards you.</p>
<p>&quot;<span style="color: purple"><em><strong>These are the author's commentary on her own works. Read them at your leisure.</strong></em></span>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Tension</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Tension</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Tension:</strong><br />
The first successful article I ever wrote for this site. Back at the beginning of 2018, I had read <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/the-cool-war-hub">The Cool War</a> and hoped to make a series of tales to rival it. Tension was supposed to be the first of this tale series, but unfortunately I lost traction shortly after publishing it. My comment on the article states &quot;more to come at a later date,&quot; and that may still be true, but I have no idea how much later.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;SCP-4084</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;SCP-4084</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p><strong>SCP-4084, Then Who Was Phone?</strong><br />
Based off a true experience of mine, this article was meant to instill a general fear of the unknown and display a case of Impostor syndrome. Within minutes of posting, the article had already gained 2 upvotes, a very positive sign indeed. Though I feel the article may be lacking an actual &quot;narrative&quot; as most SCPs nowadays do, the reception assures that sometimes its okay to be ambiguous. The less you know, the more there is to be afraid of, after all.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;The&nbsp;Gallows&nbsp;Tree</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;The&nbsp;Gallows&nbsp;Tree</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p><strong>The Gallows Tree:</strong><br />
Probably my least favorite article that I've written thus far, only because of how I limited myself. The concept of a vengeful dryad who was wrongfully convicted in life, and now goes around hanging people in a vain attempt to convict the &quot;true&quot; criminals, is a very interesting one that I should have done more with. Instead, I had the Serpent's Hand pretty effortlessly subdue her, mitigating the horror of her concept, and included a member who wanted to fuck her, reducing her even further. She started off as a horrific concept that I mitigated because I felt it was <em>too</em> horrifying. But, the SCP site is a horror website, and I've realized now that I probably shouldn't be limiting my horror on a site about horrifying people with your writing. In the future, I hope to imbue a little more raw fear, terror, and/or horror into my articles.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>Once more, she leads you down another hallway, and into a wide room that resembles an art gallery. As luck would have it, that's exactly what that is.</p>
<p>&quot;<span style="color: purple"><em><strong>As our narrator so kindly spoiled, this is The Art Gallery.</strong></em></span>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;There's&nbsp;nothing&nbsp;here&nbsp;right&nbsp;now,&nbsp;but&nbsp;you&nbsp;can&nbsp;look&nbsp;around&nbsp;anyways.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;This&nbsp;space&nbsp;is&nbsp;merely&nbsp;reserved&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;time&nbsp;being.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Nothing in here but empty frames and blank plaques.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
