<p>I've seen a lot of other authors do this, and I guess it's a pertinent enough issue that I ought to do one myself. It's highly unlikely that I'll ever decide to leave this site for good, no matter how frustrated I get I will always be determined to contribute to this community.</p>
<p>However, in the off chance that I suddenly drop off the face of the Earth due to unforeseen circumstances that may or may not involve my spontaneous death, the below guidelines should be followed when handling the future of my works.</p>
<p>- If I fail to respond to a rewrite request within two weeks, you may consider me missing in action and hereby are granted permission to rewrite the work so long as you follow my wishes.</p>
<p>- I would not like anyone to fundamentally change the core concept of any of my works when making a rewrite. I want them to remain true to what they were when first published, and if they should fail then so be it.</p>
<p>- That is just about the only guideline I have, actually. You are free to interpret my work however you like, as long as you do not fundamentally change the core concept. I am perfectly content with my works being deleted off of the site long after my disappearance due to the content of their core concept because it shows that they were ideas that were simply not meant to last.</p>
</div>
